{"title": "Art of Badminton", "description": "An instructional guide to the sport of badminton, presented by a 21-time All-England champion! Also a two-time British chess champion, his strategic acumen shines through both in his badminton and tennis tactics. One of my favourite quotes from the book perfectly captures his mindset: <i>\"I prefer to expect the best stroke my opponent has any reasonable chance of making; that is, the stroke which is most likely to cause me trouble.\"</i> - Summary by Rapunzelina", "duration": 13736, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "19342", "name": "George Alan Thomas"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1925", "genres": ["Sports & Recreation"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Rapunzelina"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Rapunzelina"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Rapunzelina"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Bruce Kachuk"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [6924], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_00_thomas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 283}, {"section": 1, "title": "I. The Racket and How to Hold it", "readers": [6924], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_01_thomas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 741}, {"section": 2, "title": "II. Footwork and Poise", "readers": [6924], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_02_thomas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1355}, {"section": 3, "title": "III. Stroke Production", "readers": [6924], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_03_thomas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1095}, {"section": 4, "title": "IV. The Smash", "readers": [6924], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/artofbadminton_2602_librivox/artofbadminton_04_thomas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 922}, {"section": 5, "title": "V. Th